-- Research In Motion Rises on Report It Plans China Applications Expansion
-- Stephen Kleege
-- 2010-07-09T15:49:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-09/research-in-motion-rises-on-report-it-plans-china-applications-expansion.html

          
          
             Research In Motion Ltd., maker of the
BlackBerry smartphone, rose the most this year after Reuters
reported the company plans to start an applications store and
consumer Internet services in China.  
 Research In Motion gained 6.3 percent to $52.57 at 11:44
a.m. in New York Stock Exchange trading after surging 6.4
percent, the most intraday since Dec. 18.  
          
          


  


        